So many people are going to lose their jobs because of this. It is a terribly kept secret in the restaurant industry that most if not all of our restaurants are in the red all the time and only a few good weeks away from closing their doors. With few exceptions we all operate at a loss. The only thing that keeps us going is that eventual good week that puts us in the black for the first time in months. If that goes away, we close. Maybe it is different for corporate chains, but for a place like where I work, we are teetering on the edge all the time.
